Lost Grenadiers

\* A more robust map program that helps the end user to find certain classrooms, offices, amenities at the campus of Indiana University Southeast. It is an extension to a previous project called Snack Map that helps the user to find certain snacks/drinks at the various different vending machines at IUS.

Proposed Software Architecture

\* Overview:

A simple yet contextual map program application of the campus of Indiana University Southeast. It assists the end user with directions, graphical display marker, and GPS locator for finding the array of buildings, rooms, and amenities. The purpose is for the project to be a tool for any current/future students, faculty, to any visitors with a ease and useful experience of finding what the information that they seek.

\* Hardware/Software Mapping

The program will run through a server where professors can utilize a back-end access screen to update where classes will be taught. Students can then enter their classes on a front-end access screen and see where they are located.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

\* Persistent Data Management

The file system/database will be kept small for the initial testing phase of this design, keeping user profile information stored locally. If scope and permissions allow, we will supply a Database Diagram showing the various relationships between entities.

\* Access Control and Security

Actors(admins, users, creators) will get most the same privileges except for the three of us who created the program and is given ultimate access to its repository, related files, and ability to change the main source code. It has a public open software license that meant to encourage unlimited access and usage from anyone who have the means to access the application. The program is meant to be open to the public and is far from the grand project goal that the three of us have for the scope of the project so we need feedback, data, and analysis to fulfill the of the project.

\* Global Software Control

Event-driven application that is activated when the end user click on the program icon.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

\* Boundary Conditions

The Lost Grenadiers is a program that will be locally/Internet hosted whether through the use of server to a cloud service provider, it is trigger when the user click on the icon of the program with its unique logo. The program will be in usage unless the operation is canceled by the user by exiting out of the program. It will respond to errors and exceptions by prompting the user with a error message box that will remove the user from that environment whether the previous session or the main menu. This program is designed with a college semester time update schedule that correlated with the opening and closing of the IUS's campus. Hopefully this program will be made available in through the cloud or be on the IU One server to ease the problem with future compatibility issues.
